
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Phase 1 as Student";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Participate</title>
    <link href="~/css/index.css" rel="stylesheet" />
    <script type="text/javascript">
        function PopUp(hideOrshow) {
            if (hideOrshow == 'hide') document.getElementById('ac-wrapper').style.display = "none";
            else document.getElementById('ac-wrapper').removeAttribute('style');
        }
        function ScreenQuestions(hideOrshow) {
            if (hideOrshow == 'hide') document.getElementById('screen-questions').style.display = "none";
            else document.getElementById('screen-questions').removeAttribute('style');
        }
        window.onload = function () {
            setTimeout(function () {
                PopUp('hide');
                ScreenQuestions('hide');
            }, 0000);
        }
    </script>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="ac-wrapper" style='display:none'>
        <div id="popup">
            <center>
                <h2 style="color: #800000;">Consent Form</h2>
                <p style="text-align:left; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #808080;">
                    The purpose of this research project is to identify if nursing students are equipped with information communication technology (ICT) skills to work in a modern healthcare setting.
                    This is a research project being conducted by Annette Stunden at Western Sydney University.
                    You are invited to participate in this research project because you are a nursing student of Western Sydney University.
                    Your participation in this research study is voluntary.
                    You may choose not to participate.
                    If you decide to participate in this research survey, you may withdraw at any time.
                    If you decide not to participate in this study or if you withdrawl from participating at any time, you will not be penalized.
                    <br><br>
                    The procedure involves filling an online survey that will take approximately 30 minutes.
                    Your responses will be confidential and we do not collect identifying information such as your name, email address or IP address.
                    <br><br>
                    We will do our best to keep your information confidential.
                    All data is stored in a password protected electronic format.
                    To help protect your confidentiality, the surveys will not contain information that will personally identify you.
                    The results of this study will be used for scholarly purposes only and may be shared with Western Sydney University representatives.
                    <br><br>
                    If you have any questions about the research study, please contact Annette Stunden at <a href="mailto:A.Stunden@westernsydney.edu.au">A.Stunden@westernsydney.edu.au</a>.
                    This research has been reviewed according to Western Sydney University IRB procedures for research involving human subjects.
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:left; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #808080;">
                    <b>
                        ELECTRONIC CONSENT: Please select your choice below.
                        <br><br>
                        Clicking on the "agree" button below indicates that:
                        <br><br>
                        • you have ready the above information
                        <br>
                        • you voluntarily agree to participate
                        <br>
                        • you are at least 18 years of age
                        <br><br>
                        If you do not wish to participate in the research study, please decline participation by clicking on the "disagree" button.
                    </b>
                </p>
                <input type="submit" name="Agree" value="Agree" onClick="ScreenQuestions('show'); PopUp('hide')" />
                <input type="submit" name="Disagree" value="Disagree" onClick="PopUp('hide')" />
            </center>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="screen-questions" style='display:none'>
        <div id="screenquestions">
            <center>
                <h2 style="color: #800000;">Screening Questions</h2>
                <p style="text-align:left; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #808080;">
                    *Please fill in the following details before continuing.
                </p>
                <form style="text-align:left; margin-left:200px;">
                    <h5 style="margin-left:-20px;">Age</h5>
                    <input type="radio" id="group1" name="age" value="group1" required>
                    <label for="group1">18-25</label><br>
                    <input type="radio" id="group2" name="age" value="group2">
                    <label for="group2">26-40</label><br>
                    <input type="radio" id="group3" name="age" value="group3">
                    <label for="group3">40+</label><br><br>
                    <h5 style="margin-left:-20px;">Gender</h5>
                    <input type="radio" id="male" name="gender" value="male" required>
                    <label for="male">Male</label><br>
                    <input type="radio" id="female" name="gender" value="female">
                    <label for="female">Female</label><br>
                    <input type="radio" id="other" name="gender" value="other">
                    <label for="other">Other</label><br><br>
                    <h5 style="margin-left:-20px;">Education</h5>
                    <label for="university">University:</label>
                    <input size="40" type="text" id="university" name="university" required><br>
                    <label for="course">Course:</label>
                    <input size="30" type="text" id="course" name="course" required>
                    <label for="year">Year:</label>
                    <select id="year" name="year" required>
                        <option value="1">1</option>
                        <option value="2">2</option>
                        <option value="3">3</option>
                        <option value="4">4</option>
                    </select><br><br>
                    <h5 style="margin-left:-20px;">Email</h5>
                    <label for="email">Email:</label>
                    <input size="30" type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
                    <br><br><br>
                    <input style="margin-left:220px" type="submit" name="proceed" value="Proceed" />
                    <input type="reset" name="cancel" value="Cancel" onClick="ScreenQuestions('hide')" />
                </form>
            </center>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="welcome" class="text-center">

        <h1 style="color: #800000;" class="display-4">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    </div>

    <div id="border">
        <img src="~/images/participate.jpg" height="400" class="img-responsive" />
        <br><br>
        <h2 style="color: #800000;">Information Sheet</h2>
        <!--Information Sheet-->
        <p style="text-align:left; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #808080;">
            <br>
            Nursing education in Australia currently teaches undergraduate nursing students’ basic digital literacy skills but is yet to
            implement e-health literacy, such as health informatics, into the undergraduate Bachelor of Nursing curricula.
        </p>
        <p style="text-align:left; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #808080;">
            The purpose of this project is to:
            <br>
            • To develop a contemporary digital literacy and health informatics skills competency framework which addresses nursing
            students’ digital literacy skills gap.
            <br>
            • Inform educators of curriculum changes required to successfully bridge the knowledge and skills gap related to digital literacy
            and health informatics of the future nurse workforce.
            <br>
            • To equip undergraduate nursing students with the appropriate graduate attributes which prepares them for the digitalised
            workforce.
        </p>
        <p style="text-align:left; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #808080;">
            This is a mixed method project which has a qualitative (phase 1) and quantitative approach (phase 2)
            Phase 2 consists of cohort A ( intervention group) and cohort B (control group)
        </p>
        <br>
        <!--Information Sheet-->
        <div style="margin-bottom: 30px;">
            <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" onclick="PopUp('show')">Proceed</button>
        </div>
        <hr style="margin-left: 150px; margin-right: 150px; margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px;">

        <p style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #808080;">
            For further information on the program, please refer to About Page (Above) or contact Annette Stunden by email at <a href="mailto:A.Stunden@westernsydney.edu.au">A.Stunden@westernsydney.edu.au</a>
        </p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>